         The proposed project is a $1.0 billion risk sharing portfolio in a trade finance facility supporting significant trade flows in Emerging Markets (EMs) through which IFC and Standard Chartered Bank (Standard Chartered) will share the risk of the portfolio on a 50-50% basis. The proposed project will augment trade limits supporting trade flows in and out of EMs at a time when the demand for trade financing far exceeds the limits offered by banks. The proposed project is expected to support continuous trade flows totaling about $4.0 billion of trade p.a. and reach over 500 companies in EMs where decreases in the level of financing is limiting trade flows..

